The evidence with the title 'Rising interest rate risk at U.S. Banks ' says Jun 24, 2014  ... Average interest rate risk in the banking system has been increasing since the end of the financial crisis and is almost back to its pre - recession level.  ... For example , a fixed - rate mortgage of 3.5 percent has a higher value when market interest rates are 2.5 percent than when market rates are 5 percent. 
